        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The keyless entry system will not respond to transmitters if ignition switch is on and the parking
                    brake is off. To use while truck is running, the parking brake must be on.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Changing the transmitter battery</emph>
        </para>
        <para>1. Insert a small coin in case slot on edge of transmitter. Twist to open.</para>
        <para>2. Remove case backing and locate battery.</para>
        <para>3. Remove battery. Replace with GP-23A equivalent. Observe (+) and (-) indicators.</para>
        <para>4. Replace case backing. Press together firmly. Test for operation.</para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Programming Additional Transmitters</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Up to 4 remote transmitters can be programmed to the system.</para>
        <para>1. Block the tires so the truck cannot roll.</para>
        <para>2. Open the driver's door.</para>
        <para>3. Turn the truck's ignition switch to the on position.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the parking brake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the programming connectors #1 and #2 at the top right of the fuse block.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect programming connector #1 with programming connector #2.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After 10-15 seconds, horn will sound 3 times. Disconnect the programming connectors.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press LOCK on the new transmitter. Horn will sound 1 time.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the ignition switch off.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply the parking brake. Test the remote transmitter for proper operation.</para>
        </step1>
