        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Changing Programming Options</emph>
        </para>
        <para>1. Block the tires, so that the truck cannot roll.</para>
        <para>2. Open the driver's door.</para>
        <para>3. Turn the truck's ignition switch to the ON position.</para>
        <para>4. Release the parking brake.</para>
        <para>5. Locate the programming circuit connectors at the top right of the fuse block.</para>
        <para>6. Connect together programming connector #1 with programming connector #2.</para>
        <para>7. After 10-15 seconds, horn will sound 3 times.</para>
        <para>8. Momentarily, disconnect the programming connectors.</para>
        <para>9. Momentarily, reconnect the programming connectors.</para>
        <para>10. Disconnect the programming connectors.</para>
        <para>11. The horn will sound 4 times.</para>
        <para>12. Use a programmed remote transmitter. Press the LOCK button to advance to the next option. The horn
            will sound a number of times to indicate the option number.
        </para>
        <para>13. Press the UNLOCK button to turn the selected option ON or OFF. The vehicle door locks will unlock if
            an option is ON, and lock if an option is OFF.
        </para>
        <para>14. Turn ignition OFF to end option programming.</para>
        <para>15. Test the remote transmitter for proper operation of programmed functions.</para>
